{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/takeRef()"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"VariantRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically you want to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_ref_sink()"},{"text":" in order to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this function is helpful."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":".  We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"where the value that is being returned already exists).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At the same time, the style of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" API makes it likely that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for newly-created ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"text":" instances, the user can be saved some","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"typing if they are allowed to return a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" with a floating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reference.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them.  The caller","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that has been converted to a full reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"text":" instance.  If ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" runs first then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reference.  If ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_take_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then the result will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an additional reference on top of that one is added.  It is best to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"avoid this situation."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib15VariantProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib7VariantC","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"takeRef()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","text":"VariantRef"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variant\/takeref()"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Variant/VariantProtocol-Implementations":{"abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/VariantProtocol-Implementations","type":"topic","title":"VariantProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variant\/variantprotocol-implementations","kind":"article"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Variant/takeRef()":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variant\/takeref()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant\/takeRef()","abstract":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"title":"takeRef()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","text":"VariantRef"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantRef":{"abstract":[{"code":"GVariant","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a variant datatype; it can contain one or more values","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"along with information about the type of the values."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","title":"VariantRef","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variantref","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VariantRef"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Variant":{"abstract":[{"code":"GVariant","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a variant datatype; it can contain one or more values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"along with information about the type of the values.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Variant","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Variant","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Variant","role":"symbol","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variant"}}}